<DOC><DOCNO> AP890707-0100 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-07-89 1304EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Vietnam     07-07 0171</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Vietnam,0176</SECOND><HEAD>Vietnam Population Grows to 64 Million</HEAD><DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Vietnam announced its population hasgrown to 64.4 million, and it called on all families to have no morethan two children.   The official Vietnam News Agency said the population had grown by11.7 million since the last census in 1979, representing a highannual growth rate of 2.13 percent.   An editorial in the Communist Party's newspaper, Nhan Dan, urgedall people to observe the national target of one or two children perfamily, the agency said.   Vietnam's already high and rapidly growing population has emergedas a major problem for the country, which faces large-scaleunemployment, a poor social and economic infrastructure anddifficulties in feeding its current population.   The most populous city in Vietnam is Ho Chi Minh City with 3.9million people, according to the census, conducted April 1. Hanoi,the capital, has 3.1 million.   The census also showed there were 2,432 people _ 1,728 women and704 men _ over the age of 100.</TEXT></DOC>